content.content:
Webhooks allow you to build or set up Simplewealth Apps which subscribe to certain
events on simplewealth.ch. When one of those events is triggered, 
we'll send a HTTP POST payload to the webhook's configured URL.

### Events

| event name | description |
| --- | --- |
| `client_created` | Any time a client is created |
| `client_updated` | Any time a client is updated |
| `client_needs_compliance` | Any time a client is updated and he/she needs to be checked for compliance |

#### client_created

```
- author (object)
    - name: `Tomas` (string)
    - email: `tomas@simplewealth.ch` (string)
- client (Client)
```

It triggers `client_created` event when a client is created. 
It also triggers `client_needs_compliance` when all internal 
checks passed and client is ready for compliance right after creation.
